resetPlaceHolder_2(); -> {
  // reset R2
  // reset R1
  if (S0 < R0)
  {
    S0 = R0;
  }
  else
  {
    ;
  }
  R0 = 0;
  C0 = C0 + 1;
}

use R sep -> R1 = R1 + sep;
resetPlaceHolder_1(); -> {
  if (S2 < R2)
  {
    S2 = R2;
  }
  else
  {
    ;
  }
  R2 = 0;
  C2 = C2 + 1;
  if (S1 < R1)
  {
    S1 = R1;
  }
  else
  {
    ;
  }
  R1 = 0;
  C1 = C1 + 1;
  // reset R0
}

abstract class SplitWorker  {
  void execute(int str)
  {

    int BOOLEAN_SEPARATOR = 102;
    int R = 0;
    lessPreciseBound((R < ((8 * str) + 8)) || (R == ((8 * str) + 8)));
    mostPreciseBound((R < str) || (R == str));
    if ((str < 0) || (str == 0))
    {
      return;
    }
    else
    {
      ;
    }
    int list = 0;
    int i = 0;
    int start = 0;
    boolean match = false;
    boolean lastMatch = false;
    int choice = ndInt2(0, str - 1);
    while (i < str)
    {
      if (!((i < choice)) && !((i == choice)))
      {
        if (match)
        {
          list = list + (i - start);
          R = R + (i - start);
          match = false;
          lastMatch = true;
        }
        else
        {
          ;
        }
        i = i + 1;
        start = i;
        continue;
      }
      else
      {
        ;
      }
      lastMatch = false;
      match = true;
      i = i + 1;
    }
    if (match && lastMatch)
    {
      list = list + (i - start);
      R = R + (i - start);
    }
    else

      ;
    }
  }
